        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 2:11AM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 211 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southwest of Fort Robinson State Park, or 36 miles southwest of
Chadron, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Belmont.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
